Nomura Appoints Mark Leahy as Head of Debt Origination for Asia Ex-Japan

-- B y   K a t r i n a   N i c h o l a s
-- 
2011-04-21T02:16:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/nomura-appoints-mark-leahy-as-head-of-debt-origination-for-asia-ex-japan.html
Nomura Holdings Inc. (8604)  hired Mark Leahy as head of debt origination and fixed income syndicate for
Asia ex-Japan as it broadens its debt business in the region.  Leahy will report to Jai Rajpal, head of fixed income for
Asia ex-Japan, and Patrick Schmitz-Morkramer, head of  investment
banking  for Asia ex-Japan, according to an e-mailed statement
from the Japanese bank.  “We are confident that Mark, in this dual role, will help
accelerate our momentum and further expand our footprint,”
Schmitz-Morkramer said in the statement.  Leahy’s previous roles include five years at Deutsche Bank
AG in  Singapore , working for the bank’s primary debt syndication
business, the statement said. He was also Asia ex-Japan head of
fixed income syndicate at UBS AG from 2001 to 2004, it said.  Most recently, Leahy co-founded Arrive Private Investments,
a brokerage business based in  Melbourne , the statement said.  Leahy will be based in Singapore and split his time between
the city-state and Hong Kong, a person familiar with the matter
said earlier today, asking not to be identified as details are
private.  “It’s great to be back,” Leahy said in the statement.
“This is an exciting and challenging role.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katrina Nicholas in Singapore at 
